# Agency-sites — General Standards

## Project structure
- `Agency-sites/` is the root workspace
- Each project lives in its own subfolder (e.g. `Assistant-H/`)
- Skills live in `.cursor/skills/` and project-specific ones in `ProjectName/Skills/`

## Code style
- Prefer vanilla HTML/CSS/JS unless a framework is explicitly requested
- Use CSS custom properties (`--var`) over hardcoded values
- Mobile-first responsive design on every project
- No inline styles — use classes

## Git workflow
- Commit after every meaningful change
- Commit message format: short present-tense summary (e.g. "Add hero section")
- Always push to GitHub after completing a feature or page

## File naming
- Lowercase with hyphens: `my-page.html`, `style.css`
- No spaces in file or folder names
